         <abstract>
            <p>Design objectives for computer music systems serving instructional purposes are discussed, and topics of research in the interactive behavior of users of such systems are outlined. The emphasis is on the need for an analysis of the cognitive processes presupposed by realizing behavioral objectives, and for an empirical theory of music interfaces that have been evolved and tested experimentally.</p>
         </abstract>
